This is for 1879,
and alexander campbell is noted.

37:32.818 --> 37:35.051
As being a proprietor
of ironmonger's court.

37:35.119 --> 37:36.953
This is the last place
where he lived.

37:36.955 --> 37:38.555
What is ironmonger's court?

37:38.623 --> 37:42.225
It's an alleyway that led off
of the main street.

37:42.293 --> 37:44.494
Ironmonger?
Blacksmith, effectively.

37:44.562 --> 37:46.562
There are three flats,

37:46.565 --> 37:51.234
And the third one
is occupied by alexander.

37:53.504 --> 37:55.772
There's a few photographs
that wou... that show.

37:55.774 --> 37:57.407
The neighborhood around there,

37:57.475 --> 37:59.643
Which was one of aberdeen's
most notorious slums.

37:59.711 --> 38:02.679
These are very heavily
subdivided tenements.

38:02.747 --> 38:04.781
So, you get numerous families.

38:04.849 --> 38:07.750
Living in incredibly
cramped conditions.

38:07.819 --> 38:10.687
The town decided to demolish
in the 1920s...

38:10.755 --> 38:14.023
Really? ...Because it was
a public health hazard.

38:14.092 --> 38:16.459
So, this aberdeen, this is
the city as it was then.

38:16.528 --> 38:18.528
That's the house...
That's the house,

38:18.596 --> 38:21.264
Ironmonger's court, where he
would've lived in his last year.

38:21.266 --> 38:22.832
Wow. And it's still there.

38:22.900 --> 38:25.635
Wow. So, it's just...
just north of here.

38:25.703 --> 38:27.603
They demolished
everything around it.

38:28.874 --> 38:30.140
So, when he died,

38:30.208 --> 38:33.009
Did he have
pretty much nothing left?

38:33.078 --> 38:36.980
Um, they don't have
a lot to their name.

38:37.048 --> 38:38.881
This is, like, a great mystery.

38:38.884 --> 38:41.684
It sounds shady as heck
to me... all of it.

38:41.687 --> 38:44.020
This is the inventory.

38:44.088 --> 38:47.023
Of the courtyard
of st. Fittick's at nigg,

