38:49.193 --> 38:50.493
There's a map in this book.

38:50.562 --> 38:52.082
Which should tell you
how to get to it.

38:52.130 --> 38:53.130
Excellent.

39:03.908 --> 39:06.276
- You ready?
- Not really.

39:06.344 --> 39:08.311
I don't know
why I'm getting emotional.

39:08.379 --> 39:10.146
I don't know them.

39:10.214 --> 39:11.981
I know.

39:11.983 --> 39:13.916
It's just kind of crazy
being here.

39:15.887 --> 39:17.987
Okay, let's go do this.

39:25.497 --> 39:27.830
Is this it?

39:27.899 --> 39:29.031
No.

39:29.100 --> 39:31.067
It's like an easter-egg hunt.

39:31.069 --> 39:33.403
Wait.

39:33.405 --> 39:35.705
Yeah, that's it.

39:35.773 --> 39:38.541
"Campbell."

39:38.610 --> 39:40.943
- I don't know why I'm emotional.
- I'm sorry.

39:40.946 --> 39:42.111
No.

39:57.162 --> 40:00.163
Did you get "alexander"
in there anywhere?

40:00.231 --> 40:01.364
Yeah, there you go.

40:01.366 --> 40:04.567
"Alexander." "alexander."

40:04.636 --> 40:06.636
I'm very happy with what I have.
Yeah.

40:06.704 --> 40:09.105
It's great, right?

40:09.107 --> 40:11.641
Ending up here and being able
to give melissa this gift.

40:11.643 --> 40:14.377
Goes beyond everything
I hoped this ride could be.

40:16.281 --> 40:17.580
It isn't often in this life.

40:17.648 --> 40:19.916
That you're able
to show true appreciation.

40:19.918 --> 40:21.584
To someone
you really care about.

40:21.652 --> 40:22.652
We found it.

40:22.720 --> 40:25.121
I know.

40:25.190 --> 40:28.558
And this is an experience
I'll hold onto forever.

40:33.130 --> 40:35.898
The germans have this word,
"fernweh,".

40:35.967 --> 40:38.234
And it's what brought us
and countless others here.

40:38.302 --> 40:39.936
To cure the homesickness felt.

40:39.938 --> 40:42.405
For a place
we've never truly known.

40:42.473 --> 40:44.207
The craziest thing
about this whole thing.

40:44.275 --> 40:47.009
Is we were shooting
"the walking dead,".

40:47.012 --> 40:51.147
Sitting between takes on this
field overlooking this cliff.

40:51.216 --> 40:52.682
Melissa, come here.

40:52.750 --> 40:53.950
And you go, "do you know
what'd be a great idea",

40:53.952 --> 40:55.318
Is to go to scotland."

40:55.386 --> 40:56.897
And I was like,
"that's what we'll do."

40:56.921 --> 40:58.321
And here we are. Here we are.

40:58.389 --> 41:01.791
From that moment,
we're at this moment.

41:01.859 --> 41:03.759
I know. That's pretty rad.

41:03.762 --> 41:05.962
But before we end our trip,
there's one more place

41:06.030 --> 41:07.964
Melissa needs to see...

41:07.966 --> 41:09.966
The last known address
of her ancestor

41:10.034 --> 41:11.835
Alexander campbell,

41:11.903 --> 41:14.504
Which, today, we found out
is still standing.

41:14.572 --> 41:16.706
- Perfect.
- Is this your bar?

41:16.774 --> 41:18.307
It is, yeah, yeah.

41:18.376 --> 41:19.942
What do you know
about this building?

41:20.011 --> 41:26.482
It... it was first used in 1777,
so it's 240 years old.

41:26.485 --> 41:29.318
And it was owned
by the mcbride family.

41:29.321 --> 41:30.720
From the what family?

41:30.788 --> 41:32.388
Mcbride family.

41:32.390 --> 41:34.490
And there's a... there's
a photograph on the wall there.

41:34.493 --> 41:36.792
I just got chills. That's crazy.

41:36.795 --> 41:38.661
Is this like coinkydink
all over the place?

41:41.733 --> 41:43.533
Wha-a-a-a-t? I gotta...

41:43.601 --> 41:46.002
Which one's who? I've gotta
get a picture of that.

41:46.004 --> 41:47.670
Mcbride... you're
on the end right here.

41:47.738 --> 41:49.205
I see.

41:49.273 --> 41:51.007
I-I need another drink.

41:51.075 --> 41:53.142
I think we hit the nail
on the head.

41:53.210 --> 41:55.411
Do you know about
next door upstairs?

41:55.479 --> 41:57.680
I know that there were
flats upstairs.

41:57.748 --> 42:01.317
On my great-great-grandfather's
death certificate,

42:01.385 --> 42:03.486
It says this is where
he passed away,

42:03.555 --> 42:05.321
14 upperkirkgate.

42:05.389 --> 42:07.223
Would've been right above
the bar, yeah. Yeah.

42:07.225 --> 42:09.225
Yeah, so the wake
would've been here.

42:11.229 --> 42:13.195
So they died right above us.

42:13.264 --> 42:16.499
I think... I think... I-I...
That's crazy.

42:16.567 --> 42:18.979
But... I mean, we've come this far
and it all leads to this bar.

42:19.003 --> 42:20.269
And it happened above us.

42:20.338 --> 42:21.904
I just feel it. I just feel it.

42:21.907 --> 42:23.105
Yeah, this is the spot.

42:25.109 --> 42:26.342
Watching you do this has been.

42:26.411 --> 42:27.777
Really fascinating,
I have to say.

42:27.779 --> 42:29.512
I've never had the desire
to look it up.

42:29.581 --> 42:31.247
I've been on my own for so long.

42:31.249 --> 42:33.082
That I've sort of
pushed it all back.

42:33.150 --> 42:35.262
It's been... it kinda makes me
wanna do it a little bit now.

42:35.286 --> 42:36.853
I'm glad we get
to do it together.

42:36.921 --> 42:38.841
Yeah, I'm glad we did it together.
Unforgettable.

42:39.991 --> 42:41.391
To alexander.

42:41.459 --> 42:42.792
Forget not.

42:44.563 --> 42:45.962
Yeah.

42:45.964 --> 42:47.897
What I can't understand.

42:47.965 --> 42:50.232
Is how I'm not
that crazy about whiskey.

42:50.301 --> 42:51.467
Maybe you're a rum girl.

42:51.535 --> 42:53.202
From the start,

42:53.270 --> 42:56.205
I knew this was destined
to be a different kind of ride.

42:56.274 --> 42:57.640
Being able to take this journey.

42:57.708 --> 42:59.408
Into the past with melissa.

42:59.411 --> 43:01.911
Has been
a truly magical experience.

43:01.979 --> 43:04.213
That we surely will forget not.

